DataElement.preferredDefinition: In image processing, a piece of information which is relevant for solving the computational task related to a certain application, either specific structures in the image itself (e.g., simple structures such as points or edges to more complex structures such as objects) or the result of a general neighborhood operation (feature extractor or feature detector) applied to the image.:Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities._A form or variant of a type or original._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
